Add an explorer (such as explorer.desktop.parts) which can be used to browse the parts in a common minimal folder experience. Here, each file type will have a default program to open it (probably kireji.app, if it is installed) (which can be overridden per-file). When double clicking parts, they are treated as folders so that they can be explored. A context menu will help usability here.

The applications "core.parts" and "abstract.parts" can possibly be forwards to the part explorer with the given part open for view. Here, consider the ability to have multiple part explorer windows open - why or why not? For example, the cardinality of the task permutation will grow with each instance of the file explorer one can have open. A finite limit will likely be required (like, for example, 3?).